biography.et: Jürgen Peil alustas karjääri filmitööstuses monteerijana ja töötas enam kui 10 aastat eri projektides nii teles kui filmis. Tema esimesed dokumentaalfilmid pälvisid kodumaal suurt tunnustust ja neid on näidatud Iiri televisioonis. Dathai pälvis Iiri Televisiooni Auhinna 2017. aastal ilmavalgust näinud telesarja "An Klondike" teise hooaja eest. Tema hiljuti valminud debüütmängufilm "Finky" pälvis suurt tunnustust Galway filmifestivalil, kus sellele anti parima operaatori auhind.
biography.en: Dathai Keane began his career as an editor and worked for over a decade cutting projects for both TV and film. His first projects as writer and director were documentaries and he has written and directed a number of award-winning documentary series for Irish television. Dathaí was awarded the IFTA for Best Director Drama at the 2017 Irish and Film Television Awards for his work on the second season of "An Klondike". He has recently completed his first feature film, "Finky". The film was funded by Screen Ireland and premiered at the Galway Film Fleadh in 2019 where it won the award for Best Cinematography.

biography.et:
Elen Lotman ESC lõpetas bakalaureuse summa cum laude audiovisuaalteose operaatori erialal Balti Filmi- ja Meediakoolis. Ta on jäädvustanud arvukalt dokumentaal-, lühi- ja mängufilme ning seoses erinevate dokumentaalprojektidega reisinud Jaapanis, Tiibetis, Hiinas, Tais, Indias, Nicaraguas, Costa Rical, Soomes ja Venemaa Arktikas. Eleni tööd on pälvinud palju tunnustust, muuhulgas 2012. aastal parima operaatoritöö eest PÖFF Tridens Herring programmis linastunud “Deemonid” eest, pälvinud eriauhinna Anapa Kinoshok filmifestivalil lühifilmi “Rambikramp” eest, tema täispikk dokumentaal “Olga” kuulus IDFA ametlikku programmi, “To My Friends” kuulus Tampere Filmifestivali rahvuslikku programmi ja Reel Heart filmifestivalil sai ta parima operaatori tiitli täispika dokumentaali “Mu kallis ema” eest. 2005. aastast õpetab Elen Balti Filmi- ja Meediakoolis operaatoritööd ning 2013-2017 juhtis seal filmiosakonda.   
Eleni doktoritöö keskendub inimese tajule ja empaatiavõimele seotuna filmitegelastega läbi kinematograafia.  
Elen on Eesti Filmioperaatorite Liidu president ning IMAGO, Rahvusvahelise Filmioperaatorite Liidu, juhatuse liige.
biography.en:
Elen Lotman ESC graduated summa cum laude from Baltic Film and Media School with BA in cinematography and has shot numerous documentaries, shorts and feature films. For various documentary projects she has travelled to Japan, Tibet, China, Thailand, India, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, US and Russian Arctic. Recognitions for her work includes 2012 Award for Best Cinematography in Black Nights Film Festival 
Tridens Herring programme for feature film DEMONS; special jury award on AnapaKinoshok Film Festival for short fiction RAMPCRAMP, official selection IDFA for full-length documentary OLGA, TO MY FRIENDS, official selection Tampere Film Festival national programme and nomination for best cinematographer on  Reel Heart Film Festival for full-length documentary MY DEAR MOTHER. Since 2005 Elen 
has been teaching cinematography in Baltic Film and Media School, in 2013-2017 she served as the head of the Film Department.  
Her PhD research focuses on aspects of human perception and empathy towards film  characters through cinematography.  
She is a President of Estonian Society of Cinematographers ESC and Member of the  Board of IMAGO, International Federation of Cinematographers.

biography.et: Mike Tait edendab DCA’s parimate rahvusvaheliste noorte- ja lastefilmide levikut lastele ja noortele vanuses 3-19. Ta korraldab iga-aastast Discovery Filmifestivali, planeerib aastaringseid kinoprogramme peredele ning aitab koolidel korraldada filmiõpet ning filmide kaasamist õppetöösse. Mike koordineerib ka Discovery Noorte Saadikute tööd - noored programmikoostajad, kes on festivali loovmeeskonna võtmeisikud. Samuti juhib ta “A-Rühma” - filmihuvilised kooliõpetajad, kes on huvitatud filmiharidusest ning filmide kombineerimisest õppekavasse.
biography.en: Mike Tait’s role at DCA (www.dca.org.uk) is to promote the very best in international film for young audiences aged between 3 and 19, and to increase audiences for these films. He produces the annual Discovery Film Festival (www.discoveryfilmfestival.org.uk), develops year-round family-friendly screening programmes and supports schools and teachers in the development of film as a valuable resource across the curriculum.  He coordinates the Discovery Young Ambassadors (DYAs) , a team of young film programmers (aged 15-19) who are a key part of the festival creative team, and also leads The A Team, a network of local schoolteachers interested in moving image education who provide classroom resources to accompany festival films.

biography.et: Minu nimi on Anna Linda Elvre, ma olen 14 aastat vana. Kuigi olen eestlane ja pärit Eestist siis alates 2. eluaastast olen elanud välismaal, sellistes riikides nagu Taani, Venemaa ja Belgia. Kolisime perega Eestisse tagasi sellel suvel. Käin praegu Tallinna Inglise Kolledžis aga eelnevad aastad olen õppinud mitmes rahvusvahelises koolis. Kandideerisin noortežüriisse, kuna ma olen huvitatud filmide analüüsimisest. Brüsselis läbisin koolis valikainena kahel aastal kursuse Understanding Film, kus me analüüsisime erinevaid filme, samuti kirjutasime stsenaariumeid ja tegin ka ühe lühifilmi. Nautisin seda kõike! Minu põhikooli loovtöö on samuti seotud filmide analüüsiga ning arvan, et žüriis olemine annab mulle juurde uusi teadmisi ja kogemusi, samas saan jagada seda, mida ise juba oskan.

Minu nimi on Helena. Olen 18-aastane ja õpin Vanalinna Hariduskolleegiumi 12. prantsuse keele klassis. Pärit olen ma Tartust, aga tulin gümnaasiumisse pealinna, et oma elu natuke huvitavamaks teha (õnnestus!). Kooli kõrvalt täidab mu päevi kinoarmastus, huvi igasuguste võõrkeelte vastu, maailma kohta rohkem õppimine ja siis õpitu üle mõtisklemine. Umbes 10. klassi alguses sain aru, et filmid tähendavad mulle midagi enamat kui lihtsalt paaritunnist meelelahutust, ja hakkasin kirjutama arvustusi nii endale, sõpradele, koolilehte kui ka blogisse. Nüüd olen vist juba omadega nii kaugel, et julgen öelda, et tahaksin filmi ka edasi õppima minna, ning proovin nüüd enda kogutud teadmistele igal pool praktikat leida - näiteks astusin sel aastal esmakordselt kriitiku rollist välja, et tegutseda sõpradega päris omaenda lühifilmi kallal.

Olen 9-aastane Võrumaa tüdruk nimega Kerstin Kalda. Ma õpin Võru Kreutzwaldi Koolis 2. b klassis. Veel õpin ma Võru muusikakoolis flööti. Mulle meeldib väga lugeda. Mul on palju lemmikraamatuid- Harry Potteri lood, ''Mässumeelsed Kassid'', Ilmar Tomuski raamatud ja paljud veel. Sel aastal hakkasin ma võrkpallitrennis käima. Ja ujumas käin ma ka. Kandideerisin lastežüriisse, sest ma tahan teada, kuidas žürii töötab, näha filme ja sellest kõigest oma klassikaaslastele rääkida.

Minu nimi on Sarah Liis Luha. Olen 12-aastane. Olen tegelenud terve oma elu laulmise ja tantsimisega ning spordiga. Samuti meeldib mulle väga näidelda ja filme vaadata. Tänu enda hobidele on mul väga suur esinemise kogemus. Olen astunud üles erinevates rollides pea kõigidel suurematel Tallinna lavadel Estonia teater, Alexela kondserdi maja, Salme kultuurikeskus jt. Õpin Tallinna 21. Kooli muusika kallakuga 6. klassis. Minu unistus on saada näitlejaks.

biography.en: Franka Potente was born 1974 in Münster (Germany). She is one of the most famous active actresses in Germany. With the world hit RUNLOLARUN by Tom Tykwer she achieved international breakthrough. After, she starred in big Hollywood productions like BLOW with Johnny Depp, THE BOURNE SUPREMACY with Matt Damon or TABOO with Tom Hardy. Besides, Franka is a successful writer (ZEHN STORIES ​(2010)​, ALLMÄHLICH WIRD ES TAG ​(2014)​) and young director. She premiered with her short film DER DIE TOLLKIRSCHE AUSGRÄBT at Berlinale in 2006 and won the Grimme award. HOME is her first feature film as a director.

biography.et: 15. aastane (novembris 16), mul on kindel soov õppida filmide tegemist pärast Tallinna Reaalkooli lõpetamist. Enamjaolt meeldivad õudusfilmid ja vahest eelistan maffiafilme („Ristiisa”, „Omad poisid”, „The Untouchables” jne.). Eriti meeldivad mulle filmid, mis mingil määral rikuvad reegleid. Olen kultuuriliselt mitmekülgne: tegelen spordiga, filmidega, muusikaga, mõttemängudega ja loen. Kui tegelen oma huvidega, siis ma olen kohutavalt põhjalik.

Oskar Roehler (snd 1959) on kaasaegse Saksa filmi üks viljakamatest ja tunnustatumatest autoritest, kes on töötanud ja töötab nii režissööri, stsenaristi kui ka ajakirjanikuna. Alates 1980. aastate keskpaigast on ta keskendunud siiski filmide lavastamisele. Tema üks esimesi auhinnatuid filme oli "No Place to Go", isiklik lugu lavastaja emast, mis esilinastus Cannes'i festivalil (Director's Fortnight sektsioon) ja pälvis Saksa filmiauhinna Lola kui aasta parim saksa film. 2010. aasta filmiga "Jew Suss: Rise and Fall" nomineeriti Roehlerit Berliinis Kuldkaru auhinnaga. Mitmed tema filmid on leidnud tee ka PÖFFi programmi. Tänavune festivali avafilm "Enfant terrible" on Roehleri pika karjääri 14. täispikk kinofilm ja see on kummardus kõige legendaarsemale Saksa filmitegijale - Rainer Werner Fassbinderile.
biography.en: Oskar Roehler (b. 1959) is a German film director, screenwriter and journalist. Since the mid-1980s he has been working as a screenwriter. Since the early 1990s he has also been working as a film director. For his film “No Place to Go”, a very personal portrait of his mother, which premiered in Cannes (Director’s Fortnight), he received the German Film Award (Lola) for best film. His 2010 film “Jew Suss: Rise and Fall” Oskar created one of his most polarizing films and was nominated for the Golden Bear at the 60th Berlin International Film Festival. “Enfant terrible” is Oskar’s latest film and homage to one of the most legendary and radical German Filmmakers - Rainer Werner Fassbinder.

biography.et: Eugen Jebeleanu on Rumeenia draama- ja filmilavastaja. On töötanud erinevates teatrites üle kogu maailma, sh Stuttgarti Riiklikus Teatris, kus ta lavastas R.W. Fassbinderi „Katzelmacheri“. Lyoni ooperimajas on tal valmimas kaasaegse ooperi projekt „I Was Looking the Ceiling and Then I Saw the Sky“ (John Adams). Tema lavastusi ja loomingut on demonstreeritud teatrifestivalidel Rumeenias, Poolas, Taanis, Saksamaal, Moldaavias ja Prantsusmaal. „Mooniväli“ on tema esimene filmilavastus.
biography.en: Eugen Jebeleanu is a Romanian theatre and film director. He has worked with prestigious theatres around the world, like the National Theatre in Stuttgart, where he directed Katzelmacher, by R.W. Fassbinder and Roosevelt Square, by Dea Loher; or the Opera de Lyon, where he is preparing a contemporary opera project, I Was Looking at the Ceiling and Then I Saw the Sky, by John Adams. His creations have been programmed in theatre festivals in Romania, Poland, Denmark, Germany, Republic of Moldova and France. "Poppy Field" is his first feature film.

biography.et: Juan Pablo Félix (snd 1983) on lõpetanud Argentina Rahvusliku filmikooli (ENERC). Pärast kooli lõpetamist töötas eriefektide projektijuhina suurimas filmiefektide tootmisele spetsialiseerunud Iberoameerika kompaniis. On töötanud filmide „The Secret in Their Eyes“ (rež Juan José Campanella, 2009), „The Headless Woman“ (rež Lucrecia Martel, 2008) ja „Carancho“ (rež Pablo Trapero, 2010) tootmises. Lavastajana teinud nii dokumentaalfilme, telesarju, lühifilme ja reklaamfilme nii Argentinas kui Hispaanias. „Karneval“ on tema debüütmängufilm.
biography.en: Juan Pablo Félix (b. 1983) graduated from Argentina National Film School (ENERC). After graduating, Juan Pablo Félix worked for seven years as General Producer and 1st A.D. at FX Stunt Team, the largest Ibero-American special effects and action design company. In particular, he worked on the movies "The Secret in Their Eyes" (dir: Juan José Campanella, 2009), "The Headless Woman" (dir: Lucrecia Martel, 2008), and "Carancho" (dir: Pablo Trapero, 2010). As a director he has worked on feature documentaries, TV series, short films, and commercials in Argentina and Spain. "Karnawal" is his first fiction feature film.

biography.et: Dmitry Rudakov (snd 1994) on lõpetanud Venemaa Riikliku Kinematograafia ülikooli (VGIK) 2016. aastal. TA osales töötubades Aleksei Utšiteli juures, kellest sai hiljem ka tema kunstiline juht debüütfilmi „Sentents“ tegemisel.
biography.en: Dmitry Rudakov (b. 1994) graduated from Russian State University of Cinematography (VGIK) in 2016, workshop of Alexey Uchitel, who later became the artistic director for his first feature film "Sententia".

biography.et: Nora Martirosyan on Prantsusmaal elav kunstnik ja filmilavastaja. Ta on lõpetanud sünnimaal Armeenias Jerevani kunstikooli ning täiendanud end Prantsusmaal (Le Fresnoy) ja Hollandis (Rijksakademie). On lavastanud mitu auhinnatud lühifilmi. Hetkel õpetab ta kauneid kunste Bordeaux’ koolis. „Kui tuul peaks vaibuma“ on Martirosjani esimene täispikk film.
biography.en: Nora Martirosyan is an artist and a film director living in France. She graduated from Art School in Yerevan, Armenia (her country of origin), from Le Fresnoy (France) and from the “Rijksakademie” in Amsterdam. She directed several award-winning short films. She is currently teaching at Bordeaux School of Fine Arts. "Should the Wind Drop" is Martirosyan's first feature film.

biography.et: BAE Jong-dae (snd 1983) on lõpetanud Korea Filmikunsti Akadeemia (KAFA). Ta on lavastanud kolm lühifilmi ja ühe täispika filmi, „Must valgus“.
biography.en: BAE Jong-dae (b. 1983) graduated from Korean Academy of Film Arts (KAFA). He directed three short films. "Black Light" is his first feature film.

biography.et: Süüria konflikti tõttu Damaskusest Dohasse lahkunud režissööride paar Rana Kazkaz ja Anas Khalaf on kirjutanud ja lavastanud viis lühifilmi. Neist viimane, „Mare Nostrum“, valiti välja Sundance’i ja Dubai festivalidel ja on osalenud kokku sajal rahvusvahelisel filmifestivalil, võites 35 auhinda. „Tõlk“ on nende esimene täispikk mängufilmilavastus.
biography.en: Rana Kazkaz and Anas Khalaf are Syrian with dual French and American nationalities. Married, they have two children and currently live in Doha afterleaving Damascus due to the Syrian conflict.They have written and directed five short films and are developing several feature films. Their last short, "Mare Nostrum", started its career in festivals with selections in Sundance and Dubai, and has now received 100 international selections and 35 awards. "The Translator" is their first full-length feature.

biography.et: Satu Tuuli Karhu is a 25-year-old actor from Finland. After graduating from University of Arts Helsinki she has worked as a freelancer in Finland's National Theatre and in several film and tv productions. Karhu was awarded with a Jussi Award for her role in Tiina Lymis' box office hit Happier Times, Grump. The Finnish Actors Association voted her for the best film actor of the year for her role in Maria's Paradise, directed by Zaida Bergroth. Next she will be seen in the lead of dramaseries called Bad Apples.
biography.en: Satu Tuuli Karhu on 25-aastane Soome näitleja. Pärast Helsingi Kunstiülikooli lõpetamist töötas ta vabakutselisena Soome Rahvusteatris ning oli kaasatud mitmetesse filmi- ja teleprojektidesse. Rolli eest Tiina Lymis’e kassahitis „Happier Times, Grump “ pälvis Satu Tuuli Jussi auhinna ning Soome Näitlejate Assotsatsioon valis ta aasta filminäitlejaks rolli eest Zaida Bergrothi filmis „Maria Paradiis “. Õige pea linastub teleseriaal “Bad Apples”, kus Satu Tuuli kehastab ühte peaosalist.

After graduating from University of Arts Helsinki she has worked as a freelancer in Finland's National Theatre and in several film and tv productions. Karhu was awarded with a Jussi Award for her role in Tiina Lymis' box office hit Happier Times, Grump. The Finnish Actors Association voted her for the best film actor of the year for her role in Maria's Paradise, directed by Zaida Bergroth. Next she will be seen in the lead of dramaseries called Bad Apples.

biography.et: Joe Marcantonio on kõrgelt tunnustatud ja auhinnatud reklaamide ja dokumentaalfilmide autor. Tema reklaamklipid Amazonile, Paul Smithile, Microsoftile, John Lewisele, Paul McCartneyle ja Nike’ile on pälvinud kõrgeid auhindu kogu maailmas. Ta on teinud ka mitu lühimängufilmi ja dokumentaalfilmi, millest 2017. a valminud „Red Light“ pälvis eri festivalidelt mitmeid auhindu. Psühholoogiline thriller „Sugulased“ on tema esimene täispikk mängufilm.
biography.en: Joe Marcantonio is a director of highly regarded film, commercial and documentary projects. His commercial work includes projects for Amazon, Paul Smith, Microsoft, John Lewis, Paul McCartney and Nike. His short film "Red Light" (2017) won numerous awards at various film festivals. Psychological thriller "Corvidae" is Marcantonio's debut feature film.

biography.et: Anna Melikjan (snd 1976) on aserbaidžaani-armeenia päritolu filmitegija, kes elab ja töötab Moskvas. Ta on lõpetanud filmirežii eriala VGIKis 2002. Rahvusvaheliselt tuntuks sai teise täispika filmiga „Merineitsi“ (2007), mis pälvis auhindu kogu maailmas, sh parima režissööri auhinna Sundance’i ja kriitikute FIPRESCI auhinna Berliini filmifestivalil. Pärast edukaid linastusi valis mainekas filmitööstuse ajakiri Variety Melikjani kümne maailma kõige lootustandvama lavastaja hulka. PÖFFil esilinastuv „Kolmekesi“ on tema kuues täispikk film.
biography.en: Anna Melikyan (b. 1976) is an Azerbaijan-Armenian filmmaker, screenwriter, producer and TV director/producer, who works in Russia. Graduated from the film directing course at VGIK in 2002. She is best known for the second full-length film "Mermaid" (2007), which received many international and national awards, including Best Director Prize at the Sundance Film Festival and FIPRESCI Prize  at the Berlin FF. After her participation at Sundance and Berlin, she was listed in the TOP-10 of most perspective film directors by "Variety" magazine. "Three" is Melikyan's sixth full-length feature.

biography.et: Julia Fleißig on LUCAS - Rahvusvahelise Filmifestivali Noortele Filmiarmastajatele, juht. Tema filmikarjäär algas filmi- ja romaanikeelte õpingute ajal, mil avas tunnustatud ja auhinnatud kunstikino, mida juhtis kuus aastat. Ta on töötanud Saksa Filmiinstituudi ja Filmimuuseumi erinevate projektidega 2006ndast aastast. Enne LUCAS filmifestivali juhiks saamist juhtis ta viis aastat filmiharidust edendavat projekti SchulKinoWochen Hessen. Julia jaoks on kino originaalne ja ehe koht, kus filme näidata, filmikultuuri elushoidmine ning ajakohastamine on talle tõeliselt südamelähedane.
biography.en:
Julia Fleißig is the Head of LUCAS – International Festival for Young Film Lovers.
During her studies of film, romance languages and literature and business, Julia opened a renowned, awarded arthouse cinema that she run for six years. She has been working in different projects at the DFF – Deutsches Filminstitut & Filmmuseum in Frankfurt since 2006. Before becoming director of LUCAS – International Festival for Young Film Lovers in 2017 she was head of the film education project SchulKinoWochen Hessen for five years. For Julia, cinema is the original and genuine place for films and she loves to keep film culture alive and vivid.

biography.et: Lauri Randla (snd 1981) on Tartus sündinud ingerisoomlane. kes on teinud varem seitse lühifilmi, millest viimane, „Mausoleum“ (2016), võitis rahvusvahelistel festivalidel üle 10 auhinna, muuhulgas ka Toronto Shorts’il parima võõrkeelse lühifilmi auhinna. Randla on lõpetanud 2015. aastal Aalto filmikooli filmirežissöörina. „Hüvasti, NSVL“ on tema esimene täispikk mängufilm.
biography.en: Lauri Randla (b. 1981) has a Bachelor’s and Master’s degree in film art from Aalto/ELO film school in Finland. His filmography to date consists of several short films, among them "Mausoleum" (2016), which has won several international awards: best foreign film at 2016 Toronto short film festival, audience prize from ShortCuts Bucharest in Romania, best film at Scanorama festival in Vilnius, London Lift-Off FF – Best Short Film, Discover Film Awards/UK - Best Narrative.Awards/UK - Best Narrative.

biography.et: Nacho Álvarez on audiovisuaalse kommunikatsioonide eriala lõpetanud hispaania-uruguai päritolu filmimees, kes on oma loomingus keskendunud kaasaegse kunsti esteetikale. Oma personaalset stiili ja vaatepunkti on ta rakendanud ka mitmes oma lühifilmis, kus ta on olnud ühes isikus lavastaja, monteerija ja operaator. Tema lavastatud reklaamklipid, moefilmid ja muusikavideod on pälvinud rahvusvahelist tähelepanu ja pälvinud preemiaid kõikjal maailmas. „Süda tuksub tuks-tuks-tuks“ on tema mängufilmidebüüt.
biography.en: Nacho Álvarez is a Spanish-Uruguayan director with a degree in Audiovisual Communications, and specialized in contemporary creation with an inclination towards aesthetics, movement and what is contemporary. With his own style and a versatile point of view, he is the director, editor and even cinematographer of many of his works. With ample experience as a director in publicity, fashion films and music videos, Nacho has won prizes both in Latin America and internationally; and his works have been shown at different festivals and cities. "My Heart Goes Boom" is his directorial debut.

biography.et: Jonas Kærup Hjort (snd 1983) on lõpetanud filmirežii eriala Taani Rahvuslikus Filmikoolis 2017 aastal. Tema lõputöö, lühifilm „In a Month“ võitis kolm auhinda (Danish Ekko Shortlist Award). 2018. PÖFFil esilinastunud „Tagantpoolt teine“ on Hjorti esimene täispikk filmilavastus.

biography.et: Nicolangelo Gelormini (snd 1978) on Itaalia režissöör, stsenarist ja monteerija. On õppinud filmi ja arhitektuuri. Alustas karjääri Oscari-võitja Paolo Sorrentino assistendina. 2008 pälvis lühifilmiga „Caro Benzina“ peaauhinna Rai Uno võistlusel. Ta on lavastanud ka mitmeid muusikavideosid ja laive Itaalia poplauljatele nagu Vivi Davvero ja Ladra Di Vento. „Fortuna – tüdruk ja hiiglased“ on tema esimene filmilavastus.
biography.en: Nicolangelo Gelormini (b. 1978) is an italian director, screenwriter and editor. He studied at Centro Sperimentale di Cinematografia after the degree in Architecture and began working as assistant to the Oscar winner Paolo Sorrentino. In 2008 he wins the Rai Uno competition show Serata d'Onore with the shortfilm "Caro Benzina". His first works as director were the music videos Vivi Davvero and Ladra Di Vento Live for the italian singer Giorgia. "Fortuna" is his first feature film.

biography.et: Bálint Nagy (snd 1986) on Ungari filmilavastaja ja operaator. Ta on lõpetanud Budapesti Teatri- ja Filmikunsti Ülikooli filmioperaatorina. On keskendunud oma töös eelkõige reklaamfilmide, videoklippide ja lühifilmide ülesvõtmisele koos pikaaegse koostööpartneri Nándor Lőrincziga (snd 1986). Pärast mitmeid edukaid ja auhindu saanud lühivorme on nad nüüd valmis saanud oma esimese ühise debüütmängufilmi „Mulle teadaolevalt“.
biography.en: Bálint Nagy (b. 1986) is a Hungarian director and DOP. He graduated from the University Of Theater and Film Arts Budapest, as a Director of Photography. He specializes in commercials, video clips and short films he brings forth together with Nándor Lőrincz (b. 1986). After a number of successful music videos and award winning short films, they now has been made their first feature film “As Far As I Know”.

biography.et: Evi Romen (snd 1967) on tunnustatud filmimonteerija, lavastaja ja stsenarist, kes elab ja töötab Austrias. Pärast Viini Filmiakadeemia lõpetamist on ta töötanud eri ametites mitmete auhinnatud mängu- ja dokumentaalfilmiprojektide juures. Võitis Austria Filmiakadeemia parima monteerija autasu Michael Sturmingeri filmi „Casanova Variation“ eest 2016. aastal. „Miks mitte sina“ on tema esimene mängufilmilavastus.
biography.en: Evi Romen (b. 1967) is the editor, author and director who currently lives and works in Vienna. After graduating from the Film Academy in Vienna with a major in cinematography and cutting, she worked as an award-winning editor of documentary films, cinema films and TV productions. She won the Austrian Film Award for "Casanova Variation" (dir: Michael Sturminger) in 2016. "Why Not You" is Romen's first feature as a director.

biography.et: Victoria Wharfe McIntyre on töötanud mitmetes reklaam- ja dokumentalistika projektides nii teatris, filmis kui teles. Ta on kirjutanud ja kaaskirjutanud mitu lühifilmi nagu „Blood on the Chandelier“, mis nomineeriti Austraalia filmiinstituudi auhinnale. Tema järgmine film „The Telegram Man“ sai BAFTAl parima välismaise lühifilmi auhinna, samuti Austraalia Kino- ja Televisiooni Akadeemia (AACTA) nominatsiooni, ning pälvis arvukalt rahvusvahelisi ja kodumaiseid auhindu. Tema viimatine lühifilm „Miro2 esilinastus 2017 Melbourne filmifestivalil, kus seda nomineeriti parima lühifilmi AACTA auhinnaga.
biography.en: Victoria Wharfe McIntyre has worked on a variety of community, commercial and documentary projects on the web and in theater, film and television. She has written and co-written several short films including "Blood on the Chandelier", which was nominated for an Australian Film Institute award. Her short film "The Telegram Man" was awarded the BAFTA LA for best foreign short, nominated for Best Short in the 2012 AACTAs (Australian Academy of Cinema and Television Arts Awards) and has won numerous international and Australian awards. Her recent short film "Miro" premiered at the 2017 Melbourne International Film Festival and was nominated Best Short Film in the 2017 AACTA Awards.

On töötanud koos mitme Poola tippoperaatoriga nagu Edward Kłosiński ja Witold Sobociński, ning osalenud operaatorina arvukates tele- ja filmiprojektides. 2007 lavastas esimese lühifilmi „Sunlight and Shadow“, mis pälvis grand prix’ Młodzi filmifestivalil. 2018 lavastas Poola telesarja „Rojst“. „25 aastat süütuna“ on tema esimene täispikk mängufilm.
biography.en: Jan Holoubek (b. 1978) graduated from the Lodz Film School (cinematography studies) in 2001. He took his first professional steps alongside such cinematographers as Edward Kłosiński and Witold Sobociński. For many years he worked as a cinematographer on numerous film and television productions. In 2007 he directed his first original film entitled "Sunlight and Shadow" that won Grand Prix at the Młodzi & Film Festival of Debut Films in Koszalin, for the best debut in a documentary film. In 2018, he directed the television series "Rojst" "25 Years of Innocence. The Case of Tomek Komenda" is his first feature film.

John Gavin Malkovich was born in Christopher, Illinois, to Joe Anne (Choisser), who owned a local newspaper, and Daniel Leon Malkovich, a state conservation director. His paternal grandparents were Croatian. In 1976, Malkovich joined Chicago's Steppenwolf Theatre, newly founded by his friend Gary Sinise. After that, it would take seven years before Malkovich would show up in New York and win an Obie in Sam Shepard's play "True West". In 1984, Malkovich would appear with Dustin Hoffman in the Broadway revival of "Death of a Salesman", which would earn him an Emmy when it was made into a made-for-TV movie the next year. His big-screen debut would be as the blind lodger in Places in the Heart (1984), which earned him an Academy Award Nomination for best supporting actor. Other films would follow, including The Killing Fields (1984) and The Glass Menagerie (1987), but he would be well remembered as Vicomte de Valmont in Dangerous Liaisons (1988). Playing against Michelle Pfeiffer and Glenn Close in a costume picture helped raise his standing in the industry. He would be cast as the psychotic political assassin in Clint Eastwood's In the Line of Fire (1993), for which he would be nominated for both the Academy Award and the Golden Globe. In 1994, Malkovich would portray the sinister Kurtz in the made-for-TV movie Heart of Darkness (1993), taking the story to Africa as it was originally written. Malkovich has periodically returned to Chicago to both act and direct.

filmography.en:
American actor, director, and producer John Malkovich has appeared in more than 70 motion pictures. He started acting in the 1980s, appearing in the films: Places in the Heart (1984) with Sally Field, Death of a Salesman (1985), The Glass Menagerie (1987), Empire of the Sun (1987), and Dangerous Liaisons (1988) with Glenn Close. His role in Places in the Heart earned him an Academy Award nomination. During the 1990s, he starred in the films: Of Mice and Men (1992) as Lennie Small, In the Line of Fire (1993) as Mitch Leary, Beyond the Clouds (1995) as The Director, The Portrait of a Lady (1996) Gilbert Osmond, Con Air (1997) as Cyrus "The Virus" Grissom, The Man in the Iron Mask (1998) as Athos, Being John Malkovich (1999) as John Horatio Malkovich, and The Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc (1999) as Charles VII. His role as Mitch Leary in In the Line of Fire earned him his second Academy Award nomination.

Malkovich went on to appear in the early 2000s films: Johnny English (2003) as Pascal Sauvage, The Libertine (2004) as Charles II, The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (2005) as Humma Kavula, Eragon (2006) as Galbatorix, Klimt (2006) as Gustav Klimt, Burn After Reading (2008) as Osborne Cox, and Changeling (2008) as Reverend Briegleb. In 2010, he co-starred with Josh Brolin and Megan Fox in the science fiction Western: Jonah Hex as Quentin Turnbull. The same year, he also starred in: Secretariat with Diane Lane, and RED with Bruce Willis, Morgan Freeman and Helen Mirren. A role he later reprised in the sequel: RED 2 (2013). Malkovich made an appearance in the science fiction action film: Transformers: Dark of the Moon (2011) as Bruce Brazos. He co-starred in the romantic zombie comedy film: Warm Bodies (2013) as General Grigio and lent his voice to the animated movie Penguins of Madagascar (2014) as the villainous octopus Dave.

As a producer, Malkovich has produced the films Ghost World (2001), The Libertine (2004), Juno (2007), and The Perks of Being a Wallflower (2012).

biography.en: Ann Sirot and Raphaël Balboni are writers and directors of fiction films.The duo came together in 2007 when they shot their first short film together, "Last Play", which is somewhat experimental, set theground work for the universe the co-directors set out to develop further in their subsequent short films, "Just the Letter T" in 2009, "The Wolf’s Version" in 2011 and "Domestic Tale" in 2012. "Madly in Life" is their first feature length film.

biography.et: Minu nimi on Gerli Rehkalt. Olen 16-aastane ja õpin Tallinna 32. Keskkooli 10. klassis. Mängin ka klaverit, tegelen sulgpalliga ja laulan kooris. Samuti on mul oma väikefirma ja panustan ka tihedalt kooli huvitegevuse arendamisse. Pean ennast väga aktiivseks ja seltskondlikuks inimeseks. Proovin alati anda endast kõik ja teha oma ülesanded võimalikult täpselt ära. Olen innukas ja õpin kiirelt.

Süüria konflikti tõttu Damaskusest Dohasse lahkunud režissööride paar Rana Kazkaz ja Anas Khalaf on kirjutanud ja lavastanud viis lühifilmi. Neist viimane, „Mare Nostrum“, valiti välja Sundance’i ja Dubai festivalidel ja on osalenud kokku sajal rahvusvahelisel filmifestivalil, võites 35 auhinda. „Tõlk“ on nende esimene täispikk mängufilmilavastus.
biography.en: Rana Kazkaz and Anas Khalaf are Syrian with dual French and American nationalities. Married, they have two children and currently live in Doha afterleaving Damascus due to the Syrian conflict.They have written and directed five short films and are developing several feature films. Their last short, "Mare Nostrum", started its career in festivals with selections in Sundance and Dubai, and has now received 100 international selections and 35 awards. "The Translator" is their first full-length feature.

Hetkel õpetab filmiteadust Rahvuslikus filmikoolis Hilajs. „Vaenlased“ on tema esimene täispikk mängufilm.
biography.en: Ali Derakhshandeh (b. 1984) began artistic career in professional cinema since 1999. He has been Director, 1st AD, programming, production manager, and casting manager in more than 35 films and series in cinema and television. Teaching at National Cinema School and Hilaj Film School. "The Enemies" is his directorial debut feature.

Ta on lõpetanud sünnimaal Armeenias Jerevani kunstikooli ning täiendanud end Prantsusmaal (Le Fresnoy) ja Hollandis (Rijksakademie). On lavastanud mitu auhinnatud lühifilmi. Hetkel õpetab ta kauneid kunste Bordeaux’ koolis. „Kui tuul peaks vaibuma“ on Martirosjani esimene täispikk film.
biography.en: Nora Martirosyan is an artist and a film director living in France. She graduated from Art School in Yerevan, Armenia (her country of origin), from Le Fresnoy (France) and from the “Rijksakademie” in Amsterdam. She directed several award-winning short films. She is currently teaching at Bordeaux School of Fine Arts. "Should the Wind Drop" is Martirosyan's first feature film.

Lisaks näidendite ja ooperite lavastamisele on ta ka tuntud dokumentaalfilmide autor, kelle töid on näidatud kõikjal maailmas. Tema mängufilm „Melanija kroonikad“ (2016) pälvis parima filmi ja režissööri preemia Läti filmiauhindade jagamisel. Läti esitas filmi poolt Oscarile, samuti osales film PÖFFi põhivõistlusprogrammis. Kairishi viimane dokfilm „Pelikan kõrbes“ (2014) pälvis auhindu olulistel dokumentaalfilmide festivalidel, sh Visions du Reel Nyonis. „Sildimaalija“ on režissööri teine mängufilm.
biography.en: Viesturs Kairišs (b. 1971) graduated from the Latvian Academy of Culture as a theatre and film director. Aside from cinema, he has been a stage director in Latvia and Germany. His previous feature film "Chronicles of Melanie" (2016) is a Latvian, Czech, Finnish co-production which got awarded the Best Fiction and Best Director at National Film Prize ceremony. The film was Latvia’s candidate for an Oscar nomination in 2017 and competed also at PÖFF's Official Main Competition. Kairish’s last documentary "Pelican in the Desert" (2014) was in competition at the Visions du Reel in Nyon, France and received special jury prize at the Let's Cee Film Festival in Austria.

Fassbinderi „Katzelmacheri“. Lyoni ooperimajas on tal valmimas kaasaegse ooperi projekt „I Was Looking the Ceiling and Then I Saw the Sky“ (John Adams). Tema lavastusi ja loomingut on demonstreeritud teatrifestivalidel Rumeenias, Poolas, Taanis, Saksamaal, Moldaavias ja Prantsusmaal. „Mooniväli“ on tema esimene filmilavastus.
biography.en: Eugen Jebeleanu is a Romanian theatre and film director. He has worked with prestigious theatres around the world, like the National Theatre in Stuttgart, where he directed Katzelmacher, by R.W. Fassbinder and Roosevelt Square, by Dea Loher; or the Opera de Lyon, where he is preparing a contemporary opera project, I Was Looking at the Ceiling and Then I Saw the Sky, by John Adams. His creations have been programmed in theatre festivals in Romania, Poland, Denmark, Germany, Republic of Moldova and France. "Poppy Field" is his first feature film.

Tema debüüt „Six Degrees of Separation from Lilia Cuntapay“ (2011) rändas mööda paljusid filmifestivale, sh Busanis. Ta on lavastanud kodumaa ühe suurema kassatuluga filmi „That Thing Called Tadhana“ (2014), mis osales ka mitmel žanrifilmide festivalil, sh Bucheonis. Täna teatakse lavastajat peamiselt suure eelarvega romantiliste komöödiate ja draamade režissöörina.
biography.en: Antoinette Jadaone, Antoinette Jadaone is an award-winning Filipina filmmaker who is a household name in both the art-house and mainstream film industry. Her debut feature, "Six Degrees of Separation from Lilia Cuntapay" (2011) has traveled to several international film festivals, including the Busan International FF. She directed one of the highest grossing independent films in Philippine cinema history, "That Thing Called Tadhana" (2014), which was also invited to big genre festivals like Bucheon International Fantastic FF. She has then helmed romantic comedies and romantic dramas supported by the biggest studios in the Philippines.

The TV movie, produced for ZDF, would go on to be nominated for the Grimme Award and was followed by scripts for the TV series "4 Blocks" and the TV movie "Jackpot". "Model Olimpia" is his first feature film.

biography.et: Frédéric Hambalek (snd 1986) on õppinud filmi ja Ameerika tsivilisatsiooni Johannes Gutenbergi ülikoolis Mainzis. Stsenaristina on ta pälvinud Tankred Torsti Auhinna käsikirja „One Man's Happiness“ eest. ZDFi produtseeritud telefilm pälvis mitu teleauhinda, sellele järgnesid stsenaariumite kirjutamine Saksa hittsarjale ja telefilmile „Jackpot“. „Olümpose modell“ on režissööri esimene täispikk filmilavastus.
biography.en: Frédéric Hambalek (b. 1986) majored in film studies and American studies at Johannes Gutenberg University Mainz. As a writer he won the Tankred Dorst Award of the “Drehbuchwerkstatt München” with his script "One Man's Happiness". The TV movie, produced for ZDF, would go on to be nominated for the Grimme Award and was followed by scripts for the TV series "4 Blocks" and the TV movie "Jackpot". "Model Olimpia" is his first feature film.

biography.et: Juan Pablo Félix (snd 1983) on lõpetanud Argentina Rahvusliku filmikooli (ENERC). Pärast kooli lõpetamist töötas eriefektide projektijuhina suurimas filmiefektide tootmisele spetsialiseerunud Iberoameerika kompaniis. On töötanud filmide „The Secret in Their Eyes“ (rež Juan José Campanella, 2009), „The Headless Woman“ (rež Lucrecia Martel, 2008) ja „Carancho“ (rež Pablo Trapero, 2010) tootmises. Lavastajana teinud nii dokumentaalfilme, telesarju, lühifilme ja reklaamfilme nii Argentinas kui Hispaanias. „Karneval“ on tema debüütmängufilm.
biography.en: Juan Pablo Félix (b. 1983) graduated from Argentina National Film School (ENERC). After graduating, Juan Pablo Félix worked for seven years as General Producer and 1st A.D. at FX Stunt Team, the largest Ibero-American special effects and action design company. In particular, he worked on the movies "The Secret in Their Eyes" (dir: Juan José Campanella, 2009), "The Headless Woman" (dir: Lucrecia Martel, 2008), and "Carancho" (dir: Pablo Trapero, 2010). As a director he has worked on feature documentaries, TV series, short films, and commercials in Argentina and Spain. "Karnawal" is his first fiction feature film.

biography.et: Dmitry Rudakov (snd 1994) on lõpetanud Venemaa Riikliku Kinematograafia ülikooli (VGIK) 2016. aastal. TA osales töötubades Aleksei Utšiteli juures, kellest sai hiljem ka tema kunstiline juht debüütfilmi „Sentents“ tegemisel.
biography.en: Dmitry Rudakov (b. 1994) graduated from Russian State University of Cinematography (VGIK) in 2016, workshop of Alexey Uchitel, who later became the artistic director for his first feature film "Sententia".

biography.et: Bálint Nagy (snd 1986) on Ungari filmilavastaja ja operaator. Ta on lõpetanud Budapesti Teatri- ja Filmikunsti Ülikooli filmioperaatorina. On keskendunud oma töös eelkõige reklaamfilmide, videoklippide ja lühifilmide ülesvõtmisele koos pikaaegse koostööpartneri Nándor Lőrincziga (snd 1986). Pärast mitmeid edukaid ja auhindu saanud lühivorme on nad nüüd valmis saanud oma esimese ühise debüütmängufilmi „Mulle teadaolevalt“.
biography.en: Bálint Nagy (b. 1986) is a Hungarian director and DOP. He graduated from the University Of Theater and Film Arts Budapest, as a Director of Photography. He specializes in commercials, video clips and short films he brings forth together with Nándor Lőrincz (b. 1986). After a number of successful music videos and award winning short films, they now has been made their first feature film “As Far As I Know”.

biography.et: Adilkhan Yerzhanov (snd 1982) võitis 1999. a Kasahstani rahvusliku telekanali korraldatud stsenaariumivõistluse, lõpetas filmirežii eriala riiklikus Kasahstani kunstiakadeemias (2009) ning töötas ja täiendas end seejärel New Yorgis. Tänaseks on Yerzhanovist saanud hinnatuim ja viljakaim Kasahstani filmitegijaid, kelle filmid pälvivad auhindu olulistel rahvusvahelistel filmifestivalidel. Kaks tema filmi, „Omanikud“ (2014) ja „Maailma õrn ükskõiksus“ (2018) on osalenud Cannes'i võistlusprogrammis. Mõlemat filmi on näidatud ka PÖFFil. Yerzhanov on Euroopa Filmiakadeemia liige.
biography.en: Adilkhan Yerzhanov, Adilkhan Yerzhanov (b. 1982) graduated from the Kazakh National Academy of Arts, as a film director in 2009 and afterwards he continued his training in New York. He is a two-time participant of the Cannes Film Festival's Official Program ("The Owners" 2014, and "The Gentle Indifference of the World", 2018, Un Certain Regard Section). Winner of “Asia Pacific Screen Awards-2019” (often referred to as “Asian “Oscars”) for “Achievement in Directing” for “A Dark, Dark Man” film. Member of the EFA (European Film Academy).
biography.ru: Адильхан Ержанов (1982 г.р.) выиграл в 1999 году конкурс сценариев, организованный Казахстанским национальным телевидением, в 2009 окончил Казахстанскую художественную академию по специальности, а затем работал и занимался самосовершенствованием в Нью-Йорке. На сегодняшний день Ержанов стал одним из самых именитых и продуктивных кинематографистов Казахстана. Два его фильма – "Собственники" (2014) и "Ласковое безразличие мира" (2018) участовали в конкурсной программе в Каннах. Оба фильма были представлены и на PÖFF. Ержанов состоит в Европейской киноакадемии.

biography.et: Oliver Rihs (snd 1971) on šveitsi režissöör, kes teeb filme väga erinevates žanrites. Ta elab ja töötab vaheldumisi nii Saksamaal kui Šveitsis. Rihs on töötanud dokumentaalfilmide lavastajana Šveitsi telejaamas SRF. 1998 valmis tema esimene lühifilm „Lilien“, mis võitis Locarno filmifestivalil parima lühifilmi preemia. Tema esimene täispikk film „Brombeerchen“ valmis 2001, kuid läbilöök tuli 2006. aasta kultuslikuks saanud teosega „Must lammas“ ja komöödiaga „Achtung, Fertig, WK!“, millest kujunes 2014. a kõige vaadatum kodumaine film.
biography.en:
Oliver Rihs (b. 1971) is a Swiss director with a wide artistic spectrum and a fable for comedy. He lives in Germany and mainly works in Germany and Switzerland. 
Up to 1997, Rihs worked as a documentary film maker for the Swiss TV-station SRF. In 1998, he realized his first short film, "Lilien", that was awarded as “Best Short Film” at the Locarno film festival that year. His first feature debut followed with "Brombeerchen" in 2001. Since then he realized several feature films, such as the Berlin-cult-movie "Black Sheep" (2006) and "Achtung, Fertig, WK!", the most successful Swiss film of 2014.

biography.et: Naël Marandin (snd 1981) on režissöör, stsenarist ja näitleja, kelle filmikarjäär algas teismelisena, kui ta osales näitlejana filmides „Les allumettes suédoises“ (The Swedish matches)  ja „La ville dont le prince est un enfant“ (The city whose prince is a child). Ta on õppinud poliitikateadust ja täiendanud end Hiinas. Pärast tagasipöördumist koju Prantsusmaale ühines kunstilise kollektiiviga KompleXKapharnauM, kellega koos tehtud lühifilmid osalesid mitmel olulisel filmifestivalil. Tema esimene täispikk film „She walks“ (2016) põhineb tõsielulisel lool Hiina prostituudist Pariisis. „Elajad“ on tema teine täispikk mängufilmilavastus.
biography.en: Naël Marandin (b. 1981) is an actor, director and scriptwriter, began acting when he was a teenager in “Les allumettes suédoises” (The Swedish matches)  and “La ville dont le prince est un enfant” (The city whose prince is a child). He took a break from these early experiences to finish his studies in Political Science and then moved to China. On his return, he worked as a video maker (with the collective KompleXKapharnaüM) and as a film director (two short films screened and awarded in numerous festivals). “She walks” (2016), his first feature film, is based on his work with Chinese women who prostitute themselves in Paris. "Beasts" is his second full-length feature.

biography.et: Byamba Sakhya on lõpetanud VGIKi operaatorina. Ta on rahvusvaheliste kogemustega dokumentaal- ja mängufilmide režissöör. Tema dokfilm „Passion“ (2010) võitis peaauhindu nii Aasia, Ameerika kui ka Euroopa filmifestivalidel, debüütmängufilm „Remote Control“ pälvis aga Busani filmifestival New Currents auhinna. Byamba on filmiproduktsioonifirma Guru Media kaasasutaja.
biography.en: Byamba Sakhya graduated VGIK as cinematographer. He is a documentary and fiction filmmaker with a long record collaboration on international film productions. His documentary "Passion" (2010) won main prizes at film festivals in Asia, the Americas, and Europe; his first feature, "Remote Control", was premiered at the Busan IFF and received the New Currents Award. Byamba is co-founder of Guru Media – a production company.

biography.et: Henrik Ruben Genz (snd 1959) lõpetas 1995. a Taani Rahvusliku Filmikooli. Samal aastal pälvis tema „Ristteed“ Müncheni tudengifilmide festivalil parima filmi ja stsenaariumi auhinna. Genzi lühifilmidest on seni edukaim olnud „Vend, mu vennake“ (1998), mis tõi talle Oscari-nominatsiooni ja Berliini festivalil Klaaskaru. Genzi esimene täispikk mängufilm „Just nagu Hodder“ (2003) on võitnud preemiaid mitmel festivalil, sh Chicagos, Londonis, Poznanis ja Zlinis. Genzi järgmised filmid „Hiinamees“, „Hirmõnnelik“, „Satisfaktsioon 1720“ ja „Jumala sõna“ linastusid PÖFFil vastavalt 2006., 2008.,  2016. ja 2017. aastal. „Erna on sõjas“ on Genzi kaheksas täispikk film.
biography.en: Henrik Ruben Genz (b. 1959) graduated in 1995 from the National Film School of Denmark. In that same year, his „Cross Roads“ won awards for Best Film and Screenplay at the Munich International Film School Festival. Of his documentaries and short dramatic films the most successful has been „Theis & Nico“ (1998), which brought him an Oscar nomination and a Glass Bear at Berlin. Genz’s first feature, „Someone Like Hodder“ (2003) was honoured by the juries of several festivals, including Chicago, London, Poznan and Zlin. His next features „Chinaman“, „Terribly Happy“, „Satisfaction 1720“ and "Word of God" were screened at PÖFF programme in 2005, 2008 2016 and in 2017. „Erna at War“ is Genz’s eight full-length feature.

biography.en: Ivaylo Hristov (b. 1955) has worked extensively as a director and actor in theatre and film. Professor of acting at the National Academy for Theatre and Film Arts in Sofia. "Fear" is Hristov's fourth full-length feature film.

biography.et: István Szabó (snd 1938) on Ungari väljapaistvamaid filmirežissööre, kes pälvis rahvusvahelise kuulsuse 1960-70ndatel aastatel filmidega „Isa“ (1966), „Armastusfilm“ (1970), „Tuletõrjuja tänav 25“ (1973) jt. Kesksel kohal Szabó loomingus on triloogia „Mephisto“ (1981), „Kolonel Redl“ (1985) ja „Hanussen“ (1988), kus kõigi kolme filmi ajaloolisi isikuid kehastab Szabó ihunäitleja Klaus Maria Brandauer. „Mephisto“ pälvis ka parima võõrkeelse filmi Oscari, triloogia teised kaks osa olid Oscarile nomineeritud. 2013 sai Szabó PÖFFilt elutööauhinna.
biography.en: István Szabó, Istvan Szabo (b. 1938) is the best-known and one of the most critically acclaimed Hungarian film directors of the past few decades. In the 1960s and '70s he directed auteur films in Hungarian, which explore his own generation's experiences and recent Hungarian history "Father" (1966); "Lovefilm" (1970); "25 Fireman Street"(1973) etc. For the public beyond art house cinema, his signature film trilogy consists of "Mephisto" (1981, winner of an Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film and a Cannes Award for the Best Screenplay), "Colonel Redl" (1984, winner of a Jury Prize at the Cannes Festival and nominated for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film) and "Hanussen" (1988, also nominated for the Oscars). His most acclaimed films came from his work with famed Austrian actor Klaus Maria Brandauer, and his ongoing collaboration and friendship with cinematographer Lajos Koltai. In 2013 he received Lifetime Achievement Award from PÖFF.

biography.et: Laila Pakalnina (snd 1962) on Läti tuntumaid režissööre, kelle dokumentaal- ja mängufilmid on pälvinud tunnustust paljudel festivalidel. Mitu tema filmi, sealhulgas „Hei, Rasma!” ja „Koidik”, on toodetud Läti ja Eesti koostöös. „Koidik” esilinastus 2015. aastal PÖFFi põhivõistlusprogrammis, pälvides parima operaatoritöö preemia. Pakalnina dokfilm „Lusikas“ osales eelmisel aastal PÖFFi Balti filmi võistlusprogrammis.
biography.en: Laila Pakalnina, Laila Pakalnina (b. 1962) graduated from the Moscow Film Institute (VGIK), Department of Film Direction, in 1991. She is Latvian director and scriptwriter who’s films have screened at Cannes, Venice, Berlinale, Locarno and Karlovy Vary, Rome and other international festivals, where they have won numerous awards. Her last full-length feature "Dawn" premiered in the Main Competition competition of PÖFF in 2015.

biography.et: Mei Feng töötab professorina Pekingi Filmiakadeemias, mille lõpetas magistrikraadiga 1998. Ta on tuntud hiina filmilavastaja LOU Ye kauaaegne koostööpartner ning kirjutanud stsenaariumeid sellistele rahvusvahelistel filmifestivalidel auhinnatud filmidele nagu „Spring Fever“ (2009, parim stsenaariumi auhind Cannes’is), „Summer Palace“ (2006) ja „Mystery“ (2012). Lavastajadebüüdi tegi filmiga „Mr. No Problem“, mis 2016. aastal pälvis auhindu Tokyo filmifestivalil ja sai parima adapteeritud stsenaariumi preemia Taipei Golden Horse auhindade jagamisel.
biography.en: Mei Feng is an associate professor at the Beijing Film Academy. He received an MA in Film Studies from the Beijing Film Academy in 1998. He is Chinese filmmaker LOU Ye’s long-time collaborator. MEI Feng is the screenwriter for "Spring Fever" (2009), which won the Best Screenplay at the 2009 Cannes Film Festival. He also co-writes "Summer Palace" (2006) and "Mystery" (2012). His directorial debut feature "Mr. No Problem" received the awards of the Best Artistic Contribution at the Tokyo Film Festival, the Best Adapted Screenplay at the Taipei Golden Horse Awards.

biography.et: Peeter Simm (snd 1953) lõpetas 1976. a Moskvas Üleliidulise Riikliku Kinematograafiainstituudi ning tegutseb filmirežissööri ja Balti filmi- ja meediakooli õppejõuna. Ta on lavastanud 11 pikka mängufilmi ja 20 dokumentaalfilmi. Tema mängufilmid on osalenud Cannes’i, Berliini ja Moskva filmifestivalil. Ta on võitnud ka Läti ja Valgevene parima filmirežissööri auhinna.
biography.en: Peeter Simm (b. 1953) has directed ten full-length features and numerous documentaries. He graduated cum laude from the Moscow Cinematography Institute in 1976, having studied under the supervision of Professor Aleksandr Stolper. He has acted as a film and stage director and screenwriter since 1977 and also teaches at the film school now.

biography.et: Bakyt Mukul (snd 1965) on Kõrgõstani näitleja ja filmirežissöör, ta on lõpetanud draamanäitleja õpingud 1993. Dastan Zhapar Uulu (snd 1988) on samuti Kõrgõstani filmitegija, lõpetanud 2010 Kõrgõstani Riikliku Kunstiinstituudi, kus ta spetsialiseerus teatrile ja kinokunstile. Mõlemad on Kõrgõstani Filmilavastajate Ühingu ja Austraaliast juhitava Asia Pacific Screen Academy (APSA) ühingu liikmed. 2016 tegid mehed oma esimese koostööfilmi „A Father's Will“, mis pälvis debüütfilmide peapreemia Montreali filmifestivalil ja seejärel veel üle 30 rahvusvahelise auhinna. „Teekond Eedenisse“ on meeste teine koostööfilm.
biography.en:
Bakyt Mukul (b. 1965) is an actor and filmmaker from Kyrgyzstan. He received training as drama actor in 1993. Dastan Zhapar Uulu (b. 1988) is a filmmaker from Kyrgyzstan. He graduated from the Kyrgyz State Institute of Arts in 2010 specializing in Theatre and Cinema. 
They both are a Members of the Union of Filmmakers of the Kyrgyz Republic and Member of the Asia Pacific Screen Academy (APSA), Australia. In 2016 they shot their debut feature film “A Father’s Will” which won the main prize for debut films "Golden Zenith" at the Montreal World Film Festival. The film won more than 30 international prizes.
They were also nominated for the Asia Pacific Screen Awards APSA in the Best Screen nomination in Australia in 2017. “The Road To Eden” (2020) is their second joint work.

biography.et: Miroslav Mandic (snd 1959) on lõpetanud Columbia ülikoolis kunstide eriala. Pärast lühikeseks jäänud filmikarjääri kodumaal Bosnia-Hertsegoviinas läks sõja eest 1990. aastate alguses pakku Tšehhi Vabariiki, kus ta lavastas rida dokumentaalfilme. Praegu elab režissöör alatiselt Sloveenias. Tema filmid on pälvinud auhindu paljudel mainekatel filmifestivalidel nagu Locarno, Chicago, Munich, Sarajevo, Melbourne ja Cairo. „Sanremo“ on Mandici kuues täispikk film.
biography.en: Miroslav Mandic (b. 1959) graduated from Columbia University school of the arts. Following a brief film career in native Bosnia and Herzegovina, during the 1990s war he immigrated to the Czech Republic, where he directed numerous documentaries. He currently lives and works in Slovenia. His films have played and won awards at a number of renowned international festivals: Locarno, Chicago, Santa Barbara, Munich, Sarajevo, Melbourne, Cracow, Cairo. "Sanremo" is Mandic' sixth full-length film.

Tema 2016. aastal valminud debüütmängufilmi „Suvi on läinud“ näidati ka PÖFFil.

His main representative short works are "The Sunday, Story Bridge" and "One Day I Looked Down". In addition, he has written a number of scripts including "The Summer Is Gone", "FUZZ", "Blue Train", and "A Star Called the Sun". His directorial debut "The Summer is Gone" was screened at PÖFF in 2016.

biography.et: Leonardo Antonio (snd 1981) alustas karjääri assistendina rahvuslikus televisioonis. Ta tegi arvukalt eksperimentaalvideosid ja reklaamfilme, katsetas kätt lühifilmidega ja töötas postproduktsiooni tiimis Mehhiko suure eelarvega linateose „The Crime of Padre Amaro“ (2005) juures. Rajas 2007 tele- ja filmiproduktsioonifirma Recycled Films. Praegu õpetab Leonardo filmi- ja teleproduktsiooni tagamaid neljas erinevas koolis. „Sõna sõna vastu“ on tema kolmas film ja esimene, mis nägi ilmavalgust uues filmistuudios Quattuor Pictures.
biography.en: Leonardo Antonio (b. 1981) worked as a  multicamera  first  assistant director in the national television.  He made lots of experimental and corporate videos as well as personal short films to   boost up experience as well as working on a mainstream film production as a post-production assistant, "O Crime do Padre Amaroin" in 2005. He founded and developed the TV &  Film  Production  Company Recycled  Films in 2007. Leonardo  is currently  teaching Post- Production,  many  modules  of  Film  and  Television,  Acting  and History  of  Animation,  Storyboarding  and  Concept  Design in  four different schools since 2015. His latest film, "Submission", is the first film of his latest company, Quattuor Pictures.

Lõpetas Zürichi Draama Akadeemia filmiga „Mise en scene“ (1977) ja töötas seejärel Colombias enam kui 40 filmi juures eri ametites. Ta on rajanud ka ühenduse „Land and Home“.
biography.en: Erwin  Goggel (b. 1949)  in  Sopó,  Colombia,  son  of  swiss  immigrants  and  entrepreneurs,  where  he  grew  up  between  poor  peasants, workers and abandoned children. Graduated  in  “Mise  en  scène”  (1977)  at  the  Schauspiel  Akademie  Zürich, has worked in Colombia on more than 40 films, going through all  the  crafts  available  in  movie  making.  He  created  the  Land  and  Home Foundation.

biography.et: Morteza Farshbaf (snd 1986) on lõpetanud bakalaurusekraadiga Teherani Kunstiülikooli filmiteaduskonna ja asunud seejärel tegema filme nii stsenaristi, lavastaja, monteerija kui ka operaatorina. Ta on teinud mitu lühifilmi ja töötanud koos Iraani suurkuju Abbas Kiarostamiga. Nii tema esimene mängufilm „Lein“ (2010) kui ka teine film „Laviin“ (2015) on osalenud PÖFFil ja pälvinud maailmas laialdast tähelepanu. „Tooman“ on Farshbafi kolmas mängufilm.
biography.en: Morteza Farshbaf (b. 1986), young Iranian director, went to the University of Art in Tehran for studying Cinema, and received his BFA in film. He has been active working in cinema as director, writer, editor and cinematographer since very early age of 18. He has directed his own short films since 2004, and made 5 short films since then. Morteza has also attended Abbas Kiarostami’s filmmaking workshops and has cooperated with him in film projects. He directed his first feature film, "Mourning" in 2010. His second feature film was "Avalanche" (2015), which premiered also at PÖFF as part of Main Competition. He runs RAS Cinematheque in Tehran that its main focus is on independent cinema from all around the world. "Tooman" is his third feature film.

biography.et: Aleksandr Mindadze (snd 1949) on lõpetanud Vene Riikliku Kinematograafia ülikooli (VGIK). Ta on üks tunnustatumaid filmistsenariste Venemaal, kelle karjäär algas juba 45 aastat tagasi. On teinud tihedat koostööd Vene režissööri Vadim Abdrashitoviga: koos on tehtud 11 filmi, millest 1995. aastal valminud „Näidend reisijale“ pälvis Berliini filmifestivalil Hõbekaru auhinna. Mindadze esimene lavastus „Otryv“ esilinastus Veneetsia kriitikute nädalal 2007. Film pälvis kodumaal nii kriitikute auhinna kui ka parima Vene debüütfilmi preemia. „Parketil“ on Mindadze neljas täispikk film lavastajana.
biography.en: Aleksandr Mindadze (b. 1949) graduated from the Russian State University of Cinematography (VGIK). He is one of the most acclaimed scriptwriters and directors in Russia with more than 20 of his screenplays produced since 1975. Early in his career, he teamed up with the acclaimed Russian director Vadim Abdrashitov, with whom he collaborated on eleven films. The Mindadze-Abdrashitov duo won the Silver Bear at Berlin in 1995 for the film "A Play for A Passenger". In 2007, Aleksandr’s directorial debut "Soar" premiered at Venice Critics’ Week. Thе film received two awards in Russia, including the Film Critics Award for the Best Debut Film. "Parquet" is Mindadze's  fourth feature film as a director.

biography.en: Jo Sol (b. 1968) is a writer and director, known for “El taxista ful” (2005), “Vivir y otras ficciones” (2016) and “Fake Orgasm” (2010). Lisaks näidendite ja ooperite lavastamisele on ta ka tuntud dokumentaalfilmide autor, kelle töid on näidatud kõikjal maailmas. Tema mängufilm „Melanija kroonikad“ (2016) pälvis parima filmi ja režissööri preemia Läti filmiauhindade jagamisel. Läti esitas filmi poolt Oscarile, samuti osales film PÖFFi põhivõistlusprogrammis. Kairishi viimane dokfilm „Pelikan kõrbes“ (2014) pälvis auhindu olulistel dokumentaalfilmide festivalidel, sh Visions du Reel Nyonis. „Sildimaalija“ on režissööri teine mängufilm.
biography.en: Viesturs Kairišs (b. 1971) graduated from the Latvian Academy of Culture as a theatre and film director. Aside from cinema, he has been a stage director in Latvia and Germany. His previous feature film "Chronicles of Melanie" (2016) is a Latvian, Czech, Finnish co-production which got awarded the Best Fiction and Best Director at National Film Prize ceremony. The film was Latvia’s candidate for an Oscar nomination in 2017 and competed also at PÖFF's Official Main Competition. Kairish’s last documentary "Pelican in the Desert" (2014) was in competition at the Visions du Reel in Nyon, France and received special jury prize at the Let's Cee Film Festival in Austria.

Auhinnatud stsenarist ning režissöör UK’st. Ta alustas filminduses lapsnäitlejana, kuid juba noore teismelisena valis pigem kaamerataguse maailma ning hakkas tegema filme. 18-aastaselt kolis Guy New Yorki, et õppida operaatoriks. UK’sse naasnud, alustas ta tööd filmisettidel, samal ajal stsenaariume kirjutades ja lavastades. 
Guy omab produktsioonifirmat nimega Zebrafish Media ning on teinud nii reklaame Nike’ile, muusika promoklippe Kanye Westile kui ka lavastanud mitmeid auhinnatud lühifilme. 2019. aastal tuli välja tema debüütfilm “Armastuse hirm”, mis linastus Just Filmil ning on pärast seda üle maailma erinevatel festivalidel võitnud mitmeid auhindu.
biography.en: Guy Davies is a multi award winning, versatile writer & director from the UK with a keen eye for visual storytelling. Originally a child actor Guy opted to pivot behind the camera age 11 and began making his own films. At 18, funded by a tuition grant, he moved to New York to study Cinematography. After graduating he returned to the UK and began working professionally in the camera department whilst writing & directing short films on the side. Guy is the founder of international production company Zebrafish Media and his experience is diverse, from commercials for Nike, music promo for Kanye West, to four award winning short films. Guy’s passion lies in narrative and his debut feature, Philophobia (2019), which gathered a dozen awards on the festival circuit worldwide and opens in cinemas across the UK on October 30th.

biography.et: Olen tegelenud video tootmise ning režiiga juba peaaegu 5 aastat ning nendest 3 Sindi Gümnaasiumi stuudioringis. Stuudioringis on meie ülesandeks teha igakuist kooli televisiooni saadet, mis kajastavad kooli sündmusi meile omapärases võtmes. Mina olen operaator, monteerija ja produtsent, ehk siis ühesõnaga teen kõike :) 2019. aastal valiti mind ka kohaliku omavalitsuse (Tori valla) aasta nooreks. Ma arvan, et olen väga kriitilise pilguga ning ei taha kindlasti asju teha nn üle käe või teeme kuidagi. Olen piisavalt motiveeritud ning täidan alati endale püstitatud eesmärgid ja plaanid.

Minu nimi on Kaarel Uueni ja olen 9-aastane. Mulle meeldib väga kinos käia ja ka kodus filme vaadata ja ma arvan, et festivalil oleks paremad ja huvitavamad filmid kui kinos.
Joonistada ja filmikangelasti meeldib mulle plastiliinist teha. Olen teinud erinevaid plastiliinist Doomi arvutimängu kangelasi ja „Vanamehe” multika maailma koos Vanamehe, laste, loomade ja majaga. Käin MaruKaru kunstistuudios Kalamajas. Suveti käime Kihnus Jaak Visnapi naivistide laagrist maalimas. Mulle meeldib legodest oma maailmu ehitada.

Minu nimi on Mari Krashevski ja ma olen kaheteist aastane. Mulle on alati filmid huvi pakkunud ja kui kinno tuleb mõni uus ning huvitav film, üritan alati seda vaatama minna.
Olen Tallinna Inglise Kolledži õpilane. Kooli kõrvalt olen tegelenud erinevate põnevate asjadega: näiteks käisin kolm aastat Hanna-Liina Võsa muusikalikoolis, mille raames esinesin Birgitta festivalil muusikalis "Muusikalicool" ja tegin kooli filmifestivalil koos sõbrannaga naljaka filmi "Taevast sajab hapukurke". Armastan koolivaheajal vanaemaga õhtuti ERR-ist häid seriaale vaadata ja asju arutada. Lisaks sellele meeldib mulle reisida ja erinevaid maid ja linnu näha.

Juanma Bajo Ulloa (snd 1967) on teenekas Hispaania filmilavastaja, kes alustas filmide tegemisega juba 14aastaselt. Tema esimene täispikk mängufilm „Butterfly Wings“ (1991), mis tõi talle noorima lavastaja tiitli, kes kunagi San Sebastiani filmifestivali võitnud, ja film „The Dead Mother“ (1993) tegid temast ühe olulisema Hispaania filmitegija. Film „Airbag“ (1997) läks ajalukku tänu sellele, et sellest sai viimase kümnendi suurim kodumaine kassahitt. „Lapsuke“ on režissööri kuues täispikk mängufilm.
biography.en: Juanma Bajo Ulloa (b. 1967) is Spanish film director. His first full-length fiction features "Butterfly Wings" (1991) in which he becoming the youngest winner in the history of the San Sebastian FF and "The Dead Mother" (1993) made him one of the main renovators of Spanish filmmaking. With "Airbag" (1997) he achieved one of the biggest box office hits of the decade. "Baby" is his sixth ful-length fiction feature.

biography.et: Fabian Driehorst on Hamburgist pärit dokumentaalfilmide ja animatsioonide produtsent. Aastal 2012 asutas ta autori ja rezissööri Frédéric Schuld’iga Fabian&Fred stuudio. Tema filmid on linastunud rohkem kui 800 festivalil ning ta on võitnud toetusi erinevatelt asutustelt nagu AFAC, Doha Filmi Instituut ja Jihlava Filmi Fond. Lisaks on ta võitnud Robert Bosch’i Sihtasutuse Filmiauhinna ning arengustipendiumi Wim Wendersi Sihtasutuselt ja Gerd Ruge’lt. Ta on osalenud Berlinale Talents 2016, Documentary Campus Mastercalls 2018, AniDox 2019 ja ACE Producers Animation 2020 treeningprogrammides.
biography.en: Fabian Driehorst is a producer of documentary and animated films, living in Hamburg. In 2012 he founded the studio Fabian&Fred with Frédéric Schuld (Author, Director). His films have been selected to over 800 festivals and he has won production grants such as AFAC, Doha Film Institute, Jihlava Film Fund and the Film Prize of the Robert Bosch Stiftung and scholarships for development by Wim Wenders Stiftung and Gerd Ruge. He has participated in the training programs Berlinale Talents 2016, Documentary Campus Masterclass 2018, AniDox 2019 and ACE Producers Animation 2020.

Born 1984 in Moscow. In 1990 my family moved to Germany, and for 2 years we lived in Cologne. After the break of the USSR we came back and I started to study at theatre school. I tried different professions  - I was a singer, my band was even a bit famous, I worked as a journalist for many famous Russian magazines. After turning 20, I started working as creative producer in the event business, i.e. film festivals and events for the biggest companies around the world. Turning 30, I made a theatre play about it in the Gogol-centre, the theatre that famous director Kirill Serebrennikov made. During the pandemic and lockdown I turned my life around and started to realise my biggest childhood dream - working as a scriptwriter and director. And here I am today.

biography.et: Nicolangelo Gelormini (snd 1978) on Itaalia režissöör, stsenarist ja monteerija. On õppinud filmi ja arhitektuuri. Alustas karjääri Oscari-võitja Paolo Sorrentino assistendina. 2008 pälvis lühifilmiga „Caro Benzina“ peaauhinna Rai Uno võistlusel. Ta on lavastanud ka mitmeid muusikavideosid ja laive Itaalia poplauljatele nagu Vivi Davvero ja Ladra Di Vento. „Fortuna – tüdruk ja hiiglased“ on tema esimene filmilavastus.
biography.en: Nicolangelo Gelormini (b. 1978) is an italian director, screenwriter and editor. He studied at Centro Sperimentale di Cinematografia after the degree in Architecture and began working as assistant to the Oscar winner Paolo Sorrentino. In 2008 he wins the Rai Uno competition show Serata d'Onore with the shortfilm "Caro Benzina". His first works as director were the music videos Vivi Davvero and Ladra Di Vento Live for the italian singer Giorgia. "Fortuna" is his first feature film.

Marko Raat is an award-winning Estonian writer-director, curator and academic, active in the fields of both arthouse fiction film and documentaries since 1999. He has a vast background in theatre directing, TV productions and in fine art. His latest feature-length documentary Funeral Diaries (2019) is still travelling the festival circuit after premiering at Dok.Fest Munich and opening DocPoint Tallinn. His most recent short film A Chairman’s Tale (2015) had its debut at the International Art Exhibition of la Biennale di Venezia. His last feature-length fiction film The Snow Queen (2010) had been developed at SOURCES2 and premiered at the Montreal World Film Festival, then was screened at Cairo and Mumbai among many acclaimed festivals.

Jaak Kilmi has graduated from the Department of Culture of Tallinn Pedagogical University, majoring in directing. He has (co-)directed and produced a string of award-winning short films; a number of documentary films and feature films. His films have received international recognition and have often been broadcasted abroad. Kilmi has acted as a member of the film commission of the Cultural Endowment of Estonia and the Estonian Film Board.

Alexey Uchitel, film director and producer, ROCK FILMS STUDIO. Alexey Uchitel founded Moscow- and Saint Petersburg-based film production company Rock Films in 1991. He has produced more than 30 award winning films that were participants of A-level film festivals. The films produced by Uchitel received nominations for the Golden Globe and have been put forward for nominations for the Oscar.

Among these films - The Fool (Ecumenical jury Prize for best film in Locarno), Bite the Dust (Cannes Official program in the section “Special screening”), The Mayor (premiered in Cannes), The Edge (Oscar Long List for the Best Foreign Language Film Nomination), Captive (Best Director in Karlovy Vary, Grand Prix in Cottbus), The Whaler Boy (Best Director’s Award at Venice Days, Venice Film Festival 2020) etc.

Alexey Uchitel’s studio Rock Films has been known for its support for first-time directors. Alexey is the President of the Message to Man International Film Festival since 2010.

biography.et: Oskar Roehler (snd 1959) on kaasaegse Saksa filmi üks viljakamatest ja tunnustatumatest autoritest, kes on töötanud ja töötab nii režissööri, stsenaristi kui ka ajakirjanikuna. Alates 1980. aastate keskpaigast on ta keskendunud siiski filmide lavastamisele. Tema üks esimesi auhinnatuid filme oli "No Place to Go", isiklik lugu lavastaja emast, mis esilinastus Cannes'i festivalil (Director's Fortnight sektsioon) ja pälvis Saksa filmiauhinna Lola kui aasta parim saksa film. 2010. aasta filmiga "Jew Suss: Rise and Fall" nomineeriti Roehlerit Berliinis Kuldkaru auhinnaga. Mitmed tema filmid on leidnud tee ka PÖFFi programmi. Tänavune festivali avafilm "Enfant terrible" on Roehleri pika karjääri 14. täispikk kinofilm ja see on kummardus kõige legendaarsemale Saksa filmitegijale - Rainer Werner Fassbinderile.
biography.en: Oskar Roehler (b. 1959) is a German film director, screenwriter and journalist. Since the mid-1980s he has been working as a screenwriter. Since the early 1990s he has also been working as a film director. For his film “No Place to Go”, a very personal portrait of his mother, which premiered in Cannes (Director’s Fortnight), he received the German Film Award (Lola) for best film. His 2010 film “Jew Suss: Rise and Fall” Oskar created one of his most polarizing films and was nominated for the Golden Bear at the 60th Berlin International Film Festival. “Enfant terrible” is Oskar’s latest film and homage to one of the most legendary and radical German Filmmakers - Rainer Werner Fassbinder.

biography.en: Danny Elfman, a four-time Oscar nominee, has established himself as one of the most versatile and accomplished film composers in the industry for over 30 years. He has collaborated with directors such as Tim Burton, Gus Van Sant, Sam Raimi, Peter Jackson, Ang Lee, Rob Minkoff, Guillermo del Toro, and David O´ Russell. Beginning with his first score on Tim Burton´s Pee-wee´s Big Adventure, Elfman has scored over 100 films, including: Milk (Oscar-nominated), Good Will Hunting (Oscar-nominated), Big Fish (Oscar-nominated), Men in Black (Oscar-nominated), Edward Scissorhands, Batman, To Die For, The Nightmare Before Christmas, Alice in Wonderland, Silver Linings Playbook, American Hustle, Justice League, Spiderman, A Simple Plan, Midnight Run, Sommersby, Dolores Claiborne. Most recently he has provided music for, Tim Burton film Dumbo for Disney, and The Grinch for Universal, and is currently working on the upcoming film The Voyage of Dr. Doolittle (2020), starring Robert Downey, Jr.
